# CSS / Styling Rules

## Naming Convention
Always use BEM with `.theme-` prefix to avoid conflicts with app-injected styles:
```
.theme-[component]__[element]--[modifier]

Examples:
.theme-hero__title
.theme-hero__cta--primary
.theme-card__image--rounded
.theme-nav__link--active
```

## Design Tokens
Use CSS custom properties for all design values — never hardcode hex/px values inline:
```css
:root {
  --theme-color-primary: #1a1a1a;
  --theme-color-accent: #e63946;
  --theme-color-bg: #ffffff;
  --theme-color-text: #333333;

  --theme-font-heading: 'Heading Font', serif;
  --theme-font-body: 'Body Font', sans-serif;

  --theme-spacing-xs: 0.5rem;
  --theme-spacing-sm: 1rem;
  --theme-spacing-md: 1.5rem;
  --theme-spacing-lg: 2.5rem;
  --theme-spacing-xl: 4rem;

  --theme-radius: 4px;
  --theme-transition: 0.2s ease;
}
```

## Approach
- Mobile-first: base styles target mobile, use `min-width` for breakpoints
- Never use ID selectors for styling — classes only
- Avoid `!important` — if required to override app styles, add a comment explaining why
- Group properties in this order: position → display/flex/grid → box model → typography → visual/color → animation

## Breakpoints
```css
/* Mobile first base styles */
.theme-hero { ... }

/* Tablet */
@media (min-width: 750px) { ... }

/* Desktop */
@media (min-width: 990px) { ... }

/* Large desktop */
@media (min-width: 1400px) { ... }
```

## App Conflict Prevention
- Never use generic class names like `.button`, `.title`, `.container` — apps use these
- Scope all styles under `.theme-` or a section-specific parent class
- When overriding app styles is necessary, scope tightly and comment clearly:
```css
/* Override Judge.me star color to match theme */
.jdgm-star { color: var(--theme-color-accent) !important; }
```
